  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 840 mg
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Pick @Thai basil{1/2%ounce} leaves from stems; mince stems and half the leaves. Reserve remaining leaves for garnish.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add shallot and cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in half the @ponzu sauce{24%milliliters} (you'll use the rest later) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer veggies to a #medium bowl{}. Cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan, if necessary.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add ginger and minced basil; cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @mushroom stock concentrate{1}(crushed), remaining ponzu, @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4 servings), and ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4). Cook until sauce is thickened and beef is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper; remove from heat.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

While beef cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper. Divide between #bowls{}; arrange beef mixture and veggies on top in separate sections. Drizzle with sriracha mayo. Garnish with @peanuts{1/2%ounce} and reserved basil leaves (tear any larger leaves first). Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.